cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.BIO, cs.CV

The paper proposes a method for seizure prediction using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) on electroencephalogram (EEG) datasets. This involves feature extraction and classification, which are common tasks in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The use of neural networks also suggests a focus on neural engineering (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper deals with medical data analysis, specifically for patients with drug-resistant epilepsy, which falls under the category of bioinformatics (cs.BIO). Finally, the paper uses Short-Time Fourier Transform (STFT) for feature extraction, which is a common technique in signal processing and computer vision (cs.CV).
